<TITLE> 10 hurt in BNP's internal clash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, May 6 (bdnews24.com) ----- At least 10 people were hurt in a clash between two factions of BNP at Jindabazar and Court Point in Sylhet on Thursday afternoon. Sounds of two rounds of firing were heard during the clash and 21 were arrested from the spot, police said. A faction, loyal to president of BNP's UK chapter, Kamaruddin Chowdhury, known as pro-Saiful group called a rally at Court Point at around 3pm on Thursday protesting the murder of a BNP leader and pressing for 21-point demand. A tension was building up between supporters of Ilias Ali and Kamaruddin over the rally from Wednesday night. Supporters of Kamaruddin led by local BNP leaders Abul Kahar Shamim and Shahariar Hossain Chowdhury brought out a procession from the party's Ambarkhana office. As the procession reached Alhamra Shopping Centre at Jindabazar, supporters of Ilias Ali intercepted triggering a chase and counter chase between the two factions. b
